06:13.985 --> 06:15.598
Look!

06:23.094 --> 06:24.728
We found it!

06:24.729 --> 06:26.930
There's a black knight
standing guard.

06:26.931 --> 06:28.465
Only one.

06:28.466 --> 06:29.715
We can take him out.

06:29.716 --> 06:30.967
Well, you perhaps
you hadn't noticed,

06:30.968 --> 06:32.960
but I'm a deckhand,
not a soldier.

06:34.839 --> 06:37.208
Then maybe
we don't <i>need</i> to fight.

06:38.910 --> 06:40.523
[ door opens ]

06:45.683 --> 06:47.266
[ groans ]

06:47.267 --> 06:49.252
I'm here on official business
for the queen,

06:49.253 --> 06:50.520
delivering
a dangerous prisoner

06:50.521 --> 06:53.165
from the kingdom
of kashyyyk.

07:01.199 --> 07:02.632
Well done, lad.

07:02.633 --> 07:04.935
The Wookiee prisoner gag...
it always work.

07:04.936 --> 07:06.002
The what?

07:06.003 --> 07:08.472
Never mind.

07:08.473 --> 07:10.240
Lock the guard in the cell.

07:10.241 --> 07:12.476
I'll be back with my mom
as soon as I can.

07:12.477 --> 07:15.045
What...

07:15.046 --> 07:16.143
[ sighs ]

07:18.516 --> 07:20.484
[ door unlocks ]

07:20.485 --> 07:23.610
[ door creaks ]

07:31.229 --> 07:32.262
Hi.

07:32.263 --> 07:33.697
My name is...

07:33.698 --> 07:34.731
Henry.

07:34.732 --> 07:36.233
Mom?

07:36.234 --> 07:37.868
[ chains rattle ]

07:37.869 --> 07:39.269
Henry.

07:39.270 --> 07:42.038
You... you remember.

07:42.039 --> 07:44.855
I knew you'd find me.

07:52.717 --> 07:53.984
I don't understand.

07:53.985 --> 07:56.152
How do you remember
when no one else does?

07:56.153 --> 07:58.179
Must have been
part of Gold's plan.

07:59.056 --> 08:01.157
My punishment in this world
is that I know the truth

08:01.158 --> 08:02.993
but I'm powerless
to do anything about it.

08:02.994 --> 08:05.295
In this world,
I'm no longer the savior.

08:05.296 --> 08:06.563
I've got no magic.

08:06.564 --> 08:07.864
That's all right.

08:07.865 --> 08:09.966
I think I know what to do.

08:09.967 --> 08:11.134
Now, come on.

08:14.005 --> 08:15.705
Oh!
Oh!

08:15.706 --> 08:18.008
<i>Henry: Uh, Killian,
this is my mom.</i>

08:18.009 --> 08:19.943
Mom, Killian.

08:19.944 --> 08:21.845
Uh...

08:21.846 --> 08:23.246
[ clears throat ]

08:23.247 --> 08:24.614
Yeah, um...

08:24.615 --> 08:25.849
[ chuckles ]

08:25.850 --> 08:27.851
Pleasure.

08:27.852 --> 08:29.152
Yeah. Right.

08:29.153 --> 08:31.121
Look, we need to... Get going.

08:31.122 --> 08:32.941
We've got a wedding
to stop.

08:37.193 --> 08:38.861
<i>Emma: Thank you
for your help, Killian.</i>

08:38.863 --> 08:40.429
<i>Hook:
Uh, yeah, of course.</i>

08:40.429 --> 08:43.215
I'm pleased you regained
your, uh, your freedom.

08:43.229 --> 08:44.984
Me too. Unfortunately,
it's not gonna last

08:44.986 --> 08:46.867
unless we put some
distance between that

08:46.893 --> 08:48.413
tower and us before
the guard wakes up.

08:51.809 --> 08:54.293
Why?

08:54.294 --> 08:56.780
Because that was not
any ordinary black knight.

08:56.781 --> 09:00.116
<i>Her name is Lily.</i>

09:00.117 --> 09:01.885
<i>She's dangerous.</i>

09:01.886 --> 09:04.358
I don't understand. What's
the problem with this Lily?

09:05.623 --> 09:06.623
[ roars ]

09:06.624 --> 09:08.306
Henry, get below now!

09:09.994 --> 09:11.894
[ roars ]

09:11.895 --> 09:13.797
I need you to load the cannon
with a chain shot.

09:13.798 --> 09:15.170
Come on! Now!

09:21.806 --> 09:23.178
Hold your fire
till I tell you!

09:26.611 --> 09:28.912
Lily, over here!

09:28.913 --> 09:30.080
Hey!

09:30.081 --> 09:31.982
[ roars ]

09:31.983 --> 09:34.043
Come on, Lily!
Come on!

09:39.390 --> 09:40.797
Now!

09:43.961 --> 09:45.162
[ screeches ]

09:51.335 --> 09:53.003
[ laughs ]

09:53.004 --> 09:54.404
That was close.

09:54.405 --> 09:55.846
[ sighs ]

09:58.209 --> 09:59.309
Cheers.

09:59.310 --> 10:01.011
You did it.

10:01.012 --> 10:02.041
<i>We</i> did it.

10:04.882 --> 10:05.882
What is that?

10:05.883 --> 10:07.083
It's goat's milk.

10:07.084 --> 10:09.319
[ scoffs ]
Where's your rum?

10:09.320 --> 10:11.921
I'm allergic.
Never touch the stuff.

10:11.922 --> 10:12.922
Of course you are.

10:12.923 --> 10:14.958
Can I ask you a question?

10:14.959 --> 10:17.294
You trusted me with your life
just now. Why?

10:18.362 --> 10:19.929
It's complicated.

10:19.930 --> 10:21.898
Might take a while.

10:21.899 --> 10:25.101
My schedule's pretty clear.

10:25.102 --> 10:27.137
Okay.

10:27.138 --> 10:29.272
Let's first work
on your fighting skills.

10:29.273 --> 10:33.258
Then we've got to help Regina
stop that wedding.

10:43.054 --> 10:45.148
Where is Regina's heart?

10:48.159 --> 10:49.806
No one?

10:50.995 --> 10:53.029
And what of the child?

10:53.030 --> 10:55.098
Surely you imbeciles
aren't all stupid enough

10:55.099 --> 10:56.900
to report back here
empty-handed.

10:56.901 --> 10:59.603
Actually, your majesty,
they are <i>exactly</i> that stupid.

10:59.604 --> 11:01.004
We would have caught
the bandit

11:01.005 --> 11:02.405
if blue
and her gaggle of uglies

11:02.406 --> 11:04.107
hadn't laid a trap
of dark fairy dust,

11:04.108 --> 11:05.475
paralyzing our axes.

11:05.476 --> 11:07.010
Always blaming the fairies.

11:07.011 --> 11:08.655
Maybe you should try

11:08.656 --> 11:10.300
and take responsibility
for once, dwarf.

11:10.301 --> 11:11.948
You mangy, flea-infested wolf.
I should get a muzzle...

11:11.949 --> 11:13.253
Silence.

11:14.719 --> 11:16.160
We aren't here to fight.

11:17.321 --> 11:18.888
We're a team.

11:18.889 --> 11:20.990
So you're not... Mad?

11:20.991 --> 11:23.017
Of course not.

11:24.328 --> 11:26.329
It's not your fault.

11:26.330 --> 11:29.099
It's <i>mine.</i>

11:29.100 --> 11:31.167
You see, I am your leader,

11:31.168 --> 11:34.037
and I have to lead
by example.

11:34.038 --> 11:39.175
We have to go
to extreme lengths to succeed.

11:39.176 --> 11:40.961
And to do that...

11:44.315 --> 11:46.375
I have to show you how.

11:48.085 --> 11:51.254
I have to motivate you.

11:51.255 --> 11:53.040
[ squish ]
[ gasps ]

11:53.924 --> 11:54.541
Aah!

11:55.893 --> 11:58.194
[ crumbling ]

12:01.432 --> 12:03.595
Well,
now you're down to six.

12:04.769 --> 12:07.069
Do you want
to make it five?

12:08.005 --> 12:11.646
Find Regina and the boy
and kill them.

12:13.911 --> 12:15.524
[ chair creaks ]

12:18.916 --> 12:21.351
[ indistinct conversations
in distance ]

12:21.352 --> 12:24.921
You're telling me
that... In this other reality,

12:24.922 --> 12:27.524
I'm an expert
with such a weapon?

12:27.525 --> 12:29.492
You're a regular
Jack Sparrow.

12:29.493 --> 12:31.194
Is that good?

12:31.195 --> 12:32.929
Here. Let me show you
how to use it.

12:32.930 --> 12:35.098
[ laughs ]

12:35.099 --> 12:37.399
Oh. [ chuckles ]

12:38.936 --> 12:40.970
They say
once you become an expert,

12:40.971 --> 12:42.505
your subconscious
takes over.

12:42.506 --> 12:44.007
Ah.

12:44.008 --> 12:46.961
Back in my world, that's what
we call muscle memory.

12:51.315 --> 12:55.084
Tell me more about this reality
you want to return to.

12:55.085 --> 12:57.287
Us, for example.

12:57.288 --> 13:00.323
I sense that we, uh...
We may be close.

13:00.324 --> 13:01.391
[ chuckles ]

13:01.392 --> 13:02.592
Very.

13:02.593 --> 13:04.294
Really?
[ chuckles ]

13:04.295 --> 13:08.298
Well, I'm starting
to get jealous of the other me.

13:08.299 --> 13:10.033
Let's see what food
Henry's discovered.

13:10.034 --> 13:12.468
I'm starving.

13:12.469 --> 13:14.048
There they are.

13:16.073 --> 13:17.574
It's as I told you,
my queen.

13:17.575 --> 13:19.909
The one-handed pirate
was helping them.

13:19.910 --> 13:22.383
And the boy was with them,
as well.

13:23.547 --> 13:25.014
Tell us
where the child is hiding!

13:25.015 --> 13:27.417
Hey! Back off, dwarf!

13:27.418 --> 13:29.519
Or they'll change your name
to "stumpy"!

13:29.520 --> 13:31.133
I know you.

13:32.122 --> 13:33.923
You're...

13:33.924 --> 13:35.225
Emma.

13:35.226 --> 13:37.060
The mad hag
who was locked in the tower.

13:37.061 --> 13:39.495
I almost didn't recognize you
out of your chains.

13:39.496 --> 13:42.065
You're the one that's hard
to recognize... both of you.

13:42.066 --> 13:43.335
This isn't who you are.

13:44.335 --> 13:47.303
Tell me...
who are we?

13:47.304 --> 13:49.605
You're my parents.

13:51.075 --> 13:53.209
I'm the product
of your true love.

13:53.210 --> 13:55.111
You taught me
how to be a hero,

13:55.112 --> 13:57.580
you taught me
how to believe in hope.

13:57.581 --> 14:00.016
And I do.

14:00.017 --> 14:03.177
And now I need <i>you</i>
to believe in it, too.

14:07.291 --> 14:09.042
You're right.

14:10.261 --> 14:12.080
Emma.

14:13.197 --> 14:16.833
Hope is
a very powerful thing.

14:16.834 --> 14:19.129
Which is why I'm going to
have to snuff it out of you

14:19.135 --> 14:21.136
and that awful son
of yours.

14:21.305 --> 14:22.305
Kill them.

14:22.306 --> 14:23.566
<i>Charming: Wait!</i>

14:25.109 --> 14:26.447
There he is.

14:27.978 --> 14:29.548
My, my.

14:29.565 --> 14:32.891
I <i>am</i> going to enjoy watching
him die in front of his mother.

14:34.619 --> 14:35.985
Save Henry.

14:36.086 --> 14:37.520
Killian,
you can't beat them.

14:37.521 --> 14:40.290
If I can help return things
to how they were meant to be,

14:40.291 --> 14:42.625
then what happens to me here
won't matter, will it?

14:43.294 --> 14:45.250
Now go.
Save your boy.

14:54.171 --> 14:56.072
Is she worth your life,
pirate?

14:56.073 --> 14:59.164
I'm willing to find out.

15:01.178 --> 15:02.448
[ grunts ]

15:04.315 --> 15:06.065
[ whimpering, gasping ]

15:11.388 --> 15:13.070
[ breathing heavily ]

15:20.297 --> 15:23.216
What do you know?
I'm a natural.

15:24.068 --> 15:26.196
Hey!

15:29.039 --> 15:31.074
What about you,
your majesty?

15:31.075 --> 15:33.176
Shall I make quick work...

15:33.177 --> 15:33.977
No!

15:33.978 --> 15:35.478
[ gasps ]

15:35.479 --> 15:37.676
I never did like pirates.

15:38.649 --> 15:40.365
Mom!

15:41.418 --> 15:43.341
[ sword plunges ]

15:46.056 --> 15:48.082
We have to
get out of here! Mom!

15:51.362 --> 15:53.215
[ whimpers ]

15:55.699 --> 15:56.625
[ gasps ]

16:05.342 --> 16:07.777
[ birds chirping in distance ]

16:07.778 --> 16:10.113
[ baby cooing ]

16:17.588 --> 16:19.407
[ door opens ]

16:22.793 --> 16:25.231
What... what's wrong?

16:27.498 --> 16:30.366
I've just learned...

16:30.367 --> 16:34.637
Of a threat to our realm.

16:34.638 --> 16:38.207
If left unchecked...

16:38.208 --> 16:41.918
It'll destroy
all that we've built together.

16:43.047 --> 16:45.148
All our happiness.

16:45.149 --> 16:48.051
But you're the Light One.

16:48.052 --> 16:50.820
Whatever this force is,
you'll overcome it.

16:50.821 --> 16:53.089
It's more complicated
than that.

16:53.090 --> 16:54.390
Eliminating this threat

16:54.391 --> 16:57.627
means I have to make
a difficult choice.

16:57.628 --> 16:59.662
And if I make the wrong one...

16:59.663 --> 17:03.199
But... You won't.

17:03.200 --> 17:05.201
You never do.

17:05.202 --> 17:08.538
You're a hero, Rumple.

17:08.539 --> 17:11.148
Yeah, but what if I'm not?

17:15.412 --> 17:17.512
Here.

17:17.512 --> 17:19.675
Things never seem quite as bleak
after a cup of tea.

17:25.222 --> 17:26.689
Belle, I'm so sorry.

17:26.690 --> 17:29.092
It's all right.

17:29.093 --> 17:30.159
It's fine.

17:30.160 --> 17:32.095
See?
It's just chipped.

17:32.096 --> 17:34.946
We can fix it.

17:36.867 --> 17:39.855
I'm not so sure
it's as simple as that.

17:43.674 --> 17:44.807
[ hurried footsteps ]

17:44.808 --> 17:45.641
<i>Henry: Mom!</i>

17:45.642 --> 17:47.110
[ gasps, sighs ]

17:47.111 --> 17:48.578
I knew you'd still be here.

17:48.579 --> 17:50.346
You again?

17:50.347 --> 17:52.115
Listen, I-I don't have time
for stories.

17:52.116 --> 17:54.650
I need to hit the road before
the evil queen has my head.

17:54.651 --> 17:56.402
Wait. I brought
someone else this time.

17:57.354 --> 17:59.589
Maybe you'll listen to <i>her.</i>

17:59.590 --> 18:01.090
[ breathlessly ]
Regina.

18:01.091 --> 18:02.892
Let me guess...

18:02.893 --> 18:04.494
You're his other mother.

18:04.495 --> 18:05.828
Emma.

18:05.829 --> 18:07.630
I have to give you credit.

18:07.631 --> 18:09.866
Breaking her out of that tower
couldn't have been easy.

18:09.867 --> 18:11.767
Henry, can you give us
a minute?

18:11.768 --> 18:12.866
Sure.

18:14.438 --> 18:17.540
You know, your son can use
some reining in.

18:17.541 --> 18:19.642
He's been
running around the forest,

18:19.643 --> 18:21.277
getting into trouble,
spouting nonsense.

18:21.278 --> 18:23.279
Regina, everything he said
about this reality...

18:23.280 --> 18:24.313
It's all true.

18:24.314 --> 18:26.149
[ scoffs ]
I doubt that.

18:26.150 --> 18:27.817
I don't know
why I'm wasting my time

18:27.818 --> 18:31.721
with a madwoman
who... Calls herself the savior.

18:31.722 --> 18:33.387
Because I can help.

18:33.490 --> 18:35.158
Your happiness
is still a possibility.

18:35.159 --> 18:36.926
Your first step is
going after the man you love.

18:36.927 --> 18:38.895
My happy ending
isn't a man.

18:38.896 --> 18:40.396
Of course not.

18:40.397 --> 18:43.499
But love is a part
of all happiness,

18:43.500 --> 18:45.301
and you have to be open to that.

18:45.302 --> 18:46.569
Go to Robin Hood.

18:46.570 --> 18:48.638
All you have to do
is tell him how you feel.

18:48.639 --> 18:49.939
Oh, is that all?

18:49.940 --> 18:51.390
You forgot
to mention the part

18:51.391 --> 18:52.842
where I'd have to
crash his wedding.

18:52.843 --> 18:54.043
What does your heart
tell you?

18:54.044 --> 18:56.997
I know what my heart says.

18:58.182 --> 19:00.883
But what if his
doesn't say the same thing?

19:00.884 --> 19:04.010
Isn't that a risk
you're willing to take?

19:06.290 --> 19:09.862
I just watched
the man I love die.

19:11.328 --> 19:12.862
I'm... I'm sorry.

19:12.863 --> 19:15.747
That's horrible.

19:15.748 --> 19:18.634
The worst part is that I never
told him I loved him.

19:18.635 --> 19:20.008
Not once.

19:21.538 --> 19:22.805
I was too scared.

19:22.806 --> 19:26.375
Too scared that...

19:26.376 --> 19:30.746
Somehow, saying it
would make it real...

19:30.747 --> 19:32.979
And change everything.

19:34.751 --> 19:37.887
But now I'll never have a chance
to take that next step with him,

19:37.888 --> 19:39.742
because he's gone.

19:42.359 --> 19:45.928
My only chance with him

19:45.929 --> 19:49.055
is if you don't make
the same mistake I did.

20:00.344 --> 20:02.335
[ indistinct conversations,
slow music plays ]

20:06.583 --> 20:09.537
[ guests murmur ]

20:12.823 --> 20:15.825
[ all panting ]

20:15.826 --> 20:17.493
We haven't heard
the wedding bells yet.

20:17.494 --> 20:19.760
There's still time.

20:30.440 --> 20:33.009
I don't even know
what to say to him.

20:33.010 --> 20:35.611
I think, in this case,
actions speak louder than words.

20:35.612 --> 20:37.480
Once you and Robin
share true love's kiss,

20:37.481 --> 20:39.541
everything
should be great again.

20:40.484 --> 20:41.891
Okay.

20:43.353 --> 20:44.987
What?

20:44.988 --> 20:47.790
You don't remember this,
but I promised you once

20:47.791 --> 20:49.370
I'd help you find
your happy ending.

20:50.861 --> 20:53.429
Just glad
I'm here to see it.

20:53.430 --> 20:54.897
You got this, Regina.

20:54.898 --> 20:58.968
I'm afraid none of you
are crashing this wedding...

20:58.969 --> 21:00.616
Dearies.

21:08.845 --> 21:10.646
Go.
I got the Dark One.

21:10.647 --> 21:12.948
"Dark One"?

21:12.949 --> 21:15.594
I'm afraid you have
the wrong name, dearie.

21:16.820 --> 21:18.921
We'll see about that.

21:18.922 --> 21:20.020
Regina, go!

21:26.596 --> 21:28.960
<i>Bishop: Let all
who have gathered here...</i>

21:33.070 --> 21:34.804
Do you, Zelena, take Robin

21:34.805 --> 21:37.105
to be
your lawfully wedded husband?

21:39.009 --> 21:40.863
I do.

21:49.486 --> 21:51.065
[ grunts ]

21:54.925 --> 21:55.988
Mom!

21:58.795 --> 22:00.345
Out of my way, boy.

22:00.346 --> 22:01.897
You have to get through <i>me</i>
to get to her!

22:01.898 --> 22:03.899
And do you, Robin,
take Zelena

22:03.900 --> 22:05.995
to be
your lawfully wedded wife?

22:21.752 --> 22:23.983
Go! You have to stop
that wedding!

22:27.624 --> 22:28.997
Robin?

22:32.963 --> 22:34.413
You won't hurt me.

22:34.414 --> 22:35.908
You're supposed to be
a hero here.

22:37.434 --> 22:40.936
And that's exactly
why I must do this...

22:40.937 --> 22:43.066
To ensure I remain one.

22:48.779 --> 22:50.846
Unh!

22:50.847 --> 22:51.808
Mom.

22:54.985 --> 22:56.667
[ grunts ]

22:58.688 --> 23:00.489
It's done.

23:00.490 --> 23:02.653
[ voice breaking ]
Mom?

23:07.764 --> 23:09.899
Regina?

23:09.900 --> 23:11.434
Mom.

23:11.435 --> 23:13.969
Why didn't you
go into the church?

23:13.970 --> 23:16.906
I...
I couldn't let you die.

23:16.907 --> 23:19.207
[ church bells ringing ]

23:27.117 --> 23:29.985
We're at the end
of the book.

23:29.986 --> 23:32.621
We're not gonna be able
to change anything now.

23:32.622 --> 23:34.990
[ laughter ]

23:34.991 --> 23:37.533
<i>Robin: [ laughing ]
Oops. Sorry.</i>

23:38.795 --> 23:40.763
Regina?

23:40.764 --> 23:42.698
Regina!

23:42.699 --> 23:44.033
<i>Zelena: Robin?</i>

23:44.034 --> 23:46.034
What's going on?

23:46.135 --> 23:47.503
Oh!

23:47.504 --> 23:49.472
Oh, now I've got blood
on my dress!

23:49.473 --> 23:50.973
Can't you see
she's injured?

23:50.974 --> 23:53.008
This is supposed to be
<i>my</i> day!

23:53.009 --> 23:55.929
And she's ruined it!

24:01.852 --> 24:04.049
It's okay.

24:05.755 --> 24:07.266
You're gonna be all right.

24:09.960 --> 24:11.560
[ voice breaking ] no.

24:11.561 --> 24:12.761
No, I'm not.

24:12.762 --> 24:15.029
No.

24:19.035 --> 24:21.237
At least I can promise you...

24:21.238 --> 24:24.844
You won't die alone.

24:27.978 --> 24:29.110
Too little, too late.

24:33.283 --> 24:34.984
Then you're gonna
change things.

24:34.985 --> 24:36.785
Return them
to the way they were.

24:36.786 --> 24:38.254
Bring back Hook.

24:38.255 --> 24:39.922
Save Regina.

24:39.923 --> 24:41.624
I can't.

24:41.625 --> 24:44.026
I'm not the Author anymore.

24:44.027 --> 24:46.362
I can't change a thing.

24:59.776 --> 25:01.610
Whoa.
Kid, what the hell?

25:01.611 --> 25:03.190
No.

25:05.181 --> 25:06.657
What's happening?

25:10.987 --> 25:13.253
He's the next Author.

25:17.127 --> 25:19.194
I-I can feel it.

25:19.195 --> 25:22.031
Henry. Fix it.

25:22.032 --> 25:23.899
Write everything
the way it was.

25:23.900 --> 25:27.197
Without ink,
he's not writing <i>anything.</i>

25:30.173 --> 25:32.708
My blood. It was
supposed to work last time.

25:32.709 --> 25:34.677
Yes, when mixed with darkness,

25:34.678 --> 25:36.612
but you're not the savior here.

25:36.613 --> 25:38.260
Because of <i>him.</i>

25:41.284 --> 25:44.053
But that doesn't mean
we didn't find one.

25:44.054 --> 25:47.089
And in this world,
we don't need a dark savior.

25:47.090 --> 25:49.291
We need a Light One.

25:49.292 --> 25:50.659
Hold on, mom.

25:50.660 --> 25:52.136
No, don't!
Henry, do it!

25:58.134 --> 26:03.038
"Thanks to the hero Regina's sacrifice,

26:03.039 --> 26:06.715
Isaac's villainous work
was undone."

26:19.889 --> 26:21.125
Henry?

26:30.033 --> 26:31.767
You did it.

26:31.768 --> 26:33.335
No, mom.

26:33.336 --> 26:35.980
<i>We</i> did.

26:41.244 --> 26:42.244
Mom!

26:42.245 --> 26:44.271
Henry.

26:48.752 --> 26:49.987
Hook.

26:55.225 --> 26:56.892
Where is he?

26:56.893 --> 26:58.861
Where's Hook?

26:58.862 --> 27:01.130
Uh, h-he was there...

27:01.131 --> 27:03.032
Right before
we got dragged away.

27:03.033 --> 27:05.734
Everyone reappeared
where they were

27:05.735 --> 27:08.070
before this whole mess
started.

27:11.141 --> 27:12.926
No.

27:14.044 --> 27:15.944
<i>Hook: Yeah,
sorry about the mess.</i>

27:15.945 --> 27:17.346
I really needed
to find that book,

27:17.347 --> 27:20.060
and I'm usually a bit tidier.

27:22.952 --> 27:24.353
Killian.

27:24.354 --> 27:26.789
[ both laugh ]

27:26.790 --> 27:27.790
[ laughing ] oh!

27:27.791 --> 27:28.888
[ laughs ]

27:30.226 --> 27:32.327
How many times
do I have to tell you, love?

27:32.328 --> 27:33.929
I'm a survivor.

27:33.930 --> 27:37.099
Look, I didn't mean
to cause any panic.

27:37.100 --> 27:39.301
I awoke
moments before your parents

27:39.302 --> 27:42.371
and came up here,
looking for your boy.

27:42.372 --> 27:44.723
He's fine.
Henry's fine.

27:44.724 --> 27:47.076
I'm just...
Glad <i>you</i> are, too.

27:47.077 --> 27:48.793
[ sighs ]

27:49.746 --> 27:51.084
What is it?

27:56.820 --> 27:59.488
When I...

27:59.489 --> 28:01.323
Watched you die...

28:01.324 --> 28:04.059
I was afraid
I was never gonna get a chance

28:04.060 --> 28:06.195
to tell you something.

28:06.196 --> 28:08.496
Tell me what?

28:10.967 --> 28:12.443
That... I...

28:16.406 --> 28:21.210
Want to thank you
for sacrificing yourself.

28:21.211 --> 28:24.852
Henry and I wouldn't have
succeeded without you.

28:26.216 --> 28:28.751
Of course, love.

28:28.752 --> 28:31.327
It's all in a day's work
for a hero.

28:50.974 --> 28:53.408
No.
W-w... wait a minute.

28:53.409 --> 28:55.177
[ grunts ]
Where are you going?

28:55.178 --> 28:57.346
Sorry... can't risk
that bum ticker of yours

28:57.347 --> 28:58.947
slowing me down.

28:58.948 --> 29:00.349
[ bells jingle ]

29:00.350 --> 29:01.717
He's all yours, lady.

29:01.718 --> 29:03.018
[ breathing shakily ]

29:03.019 --> 29:05.053
Belle.

29:05.054 --> 29:06.054
You came back for me.

29:06.055 --> 29:07.555
I came back to make sure

29:07.556 --> 29:09.057
you weren't going to try
to hurt anyone else.

29:09.058 --> 29:10.826
No, Belle.
Y-you don't understand.

29:10.827 --> 29:12.394
I only did what I...
I thought was...

29:12.395 --> 29:13.862
[ groans ]

29:13.863 --> 29:15.564
Rumple?

29:15.565 --> 29:17.144
Rumple?!

29:19.068 --> 29:20.544
[ engine revs ]

29:26.409 --> 29:27.954
[ tires screech ]

29:31.548 --> 29:33.092
[ sighs ]

29:43.827 --> 29:45.060
Wait.

29:45.061 --> 29:46.262
I need to see...

29:47.931 --> 29:50.299
Not on that list?

29:50.300 --> 29:54.937
No best-seller,
no fans, no awards.

29:54.938 --> 29:57.539
It's all gone.

29:57.540 --> 29:59.208
My life.

29:59.209 --> 30:00.576
I need to know.

30:00.577 --> 30:03.245
Years ago,
you set us on a path

30:03.246 --> 30:05.180
to hurt maleficent
and her daughter.

30:05.181 --> 30:08.203
Why'd you want to hurt us
so badly?

30:09.853 --> 30:13.021
The truth, "Charming"?

30:13.022 --> 30:16.560
It's not you,
but who you represent.

30:18.027 --> 30:20.462
You remind me of a boss
that I once had.

30:20.463 --> 30:23.465
One bad boss
started all this?

30:23.466 --> 30:25.934
A <i>lifetime</i> of bad bosses...

30:25.935 --> 30:28.570
Of people like you,
who fancy themselves heroes,

30:28.571 --> 30:32.474
pushing around
people like me.

30:32.475 --> 30:35.085
It was <i>my</i> turn to win.

30:36.145 --> 30:38.013
To be the hero.

30:38.014 --> 30:40.382
But you became a villain.

30:40.383 --> 30:43.518
'Cause that's
what villains do...

30:43.519 --> 30:48.156
They make themselves happy
at the expense of others.

30:48.157 --> 30:51.248
But it just makes them
more unhappy.

30:52.962 --> 30:56.164
I know what it is
to feel your heart go dark.

30:56.165 --> 30:58.667
And that...

30:58.668 --> 31:02.446
That isn't
something to idolize.

31:03.907 --> 31:06.138
It's something to pity.

31:17.220 --> 31:20.222
It <i>is</i> tempting, is it not?

31:20.223 --> 31:23.592
The power of the quill?

31:23.593 --> 31:26.094
I-I just keep thinking...

31:26.095 --> 31:29.393
Maybe I could use it
just one more time...

31:31.100 --> 31:32.935
To bring back my dad.

31:32.936 --> 31:35.671
[ sighs ]

31:35.672 --> 31:37.139
Henry...

31:37.140 --> 31:42.110
Not even an Author
can bring back the dead,

31:42.111 --> 31:44.446
no matter how much
they might wish it.

31:44.447 --> 31:47.416
But Hook was dead, and then
I brought him back to life...

31:47.417 --> 31:49.584
Hook's death
was never real.

31:49.585 --> 31:52.087
That was a fiction
created by Isaac.

31:52.088 --> 31:54.957
And now, thanks to you,
that fiction has been erased.

31:54.958 --> 31:57.327
You see?

31:58.628 --> 32:01.897
All gone.

32:01.898 --> 32:08.637
But your father, Baelfire,
died in the <i>real</i> world.

32:08.638 --> 32:13.075
And that, sadly,
can never be undone.

32:13.076 --> 32:16.111
The best way to show your love
for those that are gone

32:16.112 --> 32:19.753
is to tell their stories.

32:21.184 --> 32:24.343
Now, this book, these stories...

32:26.556 --> 32:29.524
Can never be erased, because...

32:29.525 --> 32:32.127
They are more than stories.

32:32.128 --> 32:34.394
They are the truth.

32:36.032 --> 32:39.768
And the truth
is what you must write.

32:39.769 --> 32:45.609
I hope that you can resist
the temptation of the quill.

32:48.111 --> 32:51.146
The power to change reality

32:51.147 --> 32:55.132
is only outweighed
by the cost.

33:02.792 --> 33:06.330
No one should have
that much power.

33:07.630 --> 33:10.432
It would seem that,
this time,

33:10.433 --> 33:14.349
we have found
the right person for the job.

33:18.107 --> 33:19.207
[ groans ]

33:19.208 --> 33:21.143
Hey.

33:21.144 --> 33:23.078
What's happening?

33:23.079 --> 33:25.781
It's my heart.

33:25.782 --> 33:30.452
The last human fleck of red...
Is disappearing.

33:30.453 --> 33:33.132
Your ability to love.

33:34.357 --> 33:37.626
At least, in the end...

33:37.627 --> 33:39.394
I got one last taste.

33:39.395 --> 33:41.196
[ breathing heavily ]

33:41.197 --> 33:43.698
We were happy in there.

33:43.699 --> 33:45.133
We were in love.

33:45.134 --> 33:47.369
[ chuckles softly ]

33:47.370 --> 33:49.327
I was <i>already</i> in love.

33:51.474 --> 33:54.443
Everything we had in the book,

33:54.444 --> 33:56.211
you... you could have had
<i>here.</i>

33:56.212 --> 34:01.083
You could have been a good man
with a good marriage for real.

34:01.084 --> 34:03.552
Why wasn't it good enough?

34:03.553 --> 34:06.437
Because
I didn't believe it.

34:08.391 --> 34:10.391
[ voice breaking ]
Who could ever love me?

34:10.393 --> 34:13.428
I knew what I was getting, Rumple.

34:13.429 --> 34:16.197
I-I wasn't
going to pull back.

34:16.199 --> 34:19.467
But I made you do
just that.

34:19.469 --> 34:21.203
[ inhales shakily ]

34:21.204 --> 34:24.539
There's a whole world out there,
Belle, for you.

34:24.540 --> 34:25.639
Go with Will.

34:25.641 --> 34:28.697
I don't love Will.

34:30.612 --> 34:34.288
And I'm not letting you
die alone.

34:36.152 --> 34:38.246
[ sniffles ]

34:42.725 --> 34:46.161
Go far away.

34:46.161 --> 34:49.297
When the man is gone...

34:49.297 --> 34:53.168
Only the Dark One remains.

34:53.168 --> 34:54.469
And that is more...

34:54.469 --> 34:55.469
[ groans ]

34:55.471 --> 34:57.139
That's more dangerous than...

34:57.139 --> 34:58.473
[ sniffles ]

34:58.474 --> 35:00.675
[ hoarsely ]
You can ever imagi...

35:00.676 --> 35:01.643
Aah!

35:01.644 --> 35:02.911
Rumple!

35:02.912 --> 35:05.480
[ groans ]

35:05.481 --> 35:07.149
Rumple!

35:07.150 --> 35:08.694
[ sobs ]

35:12.388 --> 35:15.423
[ indistinct conversations ]

35:15.424 --> 35:18.827
<i>âª Wash away my troubles,
wash away my pain âª</i>

35:18.828 --> 35:22.430
<i>âª with the rain in shambala âª</i>

35:22.431 --> 35:24.166
<i>âª wash away my sorrow âª</i>

35:24.167 --> 35:24.833
Hello.

35:24.834 --> 35:26.535
<i>âª Wash away my shame âª</i>

35:26.536 --> 35:29.271
So, not to puncture the party,

35:29.272 --> 35:31.239
but did you check on Zelena?

35:31.240 --> 35:34.606
Still locked up, still pregnant.

35:35.878 --> 35:39.347
But that's something
we'll be able to deal with.

35:40.616 --> 35:41.920
Together.

35:43.352 --> 35:46.688
So, Will is looking after Roland.

35:46.689 --> 35:50.225
Perhaps I could take you
for a walk in the moonlight?

35:50.226 --> 35:52.360
[ chuckles ]

35:52.361 --> 35:53.628
Perhaps.

35:53.629 --> 35:56.798
<i>âª Everyone is lucky,
everyone is so kind âª</i>

35:56.799 --> 35:57.832
<i>âª on the road to shambala âª</i>

35:57.833 --> 35:59.601
I didn't mean to kill you.

35:59.602 --> 36:02.337
Though, to be fair,
I didn't have a heart.

36:02.338 --> 36:03.505
So it's <i>my</i> fault?

36:03.506 --> 36:06.374
What I <i>think</i>
he means to say is...

36:06.375 --> 36:08.343
We are sorry.

36:08.344 --> 36:09.945
Eh, you don't need
to be sorry.

36:09.946 --> 36:11.746
Although I do intend
to hold it over your heads

36:11.747 --> 36:13.230
for a very long time.

36:13.231 --> 36:14.716
I think we both know
what happened in that world

36:14.717 --> 36:17.301
was not real.

36:17.302 --> 36:19.888
Although, seeing you guys
as real villains made me sorry

36:19.889 --> 36:23.692
for holding a grudge against you
for so long.

36:23.693 --> 36:27.395
<i>âª How does your light shine
in the halls... âª</i>

36:27.396 --> 36:29.010
<i>Emma:
Give me a second.</i>

36:30.666 --> 36:31.933
Hey.

36:31.934 --> 36:35.369
What's up?
Something wrong?

36:36.272 --> 36:38.607
Do you remember this?

36:38.608 --> 36:39.941
Yeah.

36:39.942 --> 36:41.276
I nearly got hepatitis
stealing it back

36:41.277 --> 36:42.944
from your boyfriend's
rat-infested place.

36:42.945 --> 36:45.814
It's a piece of the egg
I was hatched from.

36:45.815 --> 36:49.284
It's also the only clue I have
as to who my father is.

36:49.285 --> 36:50.785
Have you asked your mother?

36:50.786 --> 36:51.953
She doesn't know, either.

36:51.954 --> 36:53.021
What?

36:53.022 --> 36:55.290
It's a dragon thing.

36:55.291 --> 36:58.004
You know, it... Happened
in dragon form.

36:59.895 --> 37:02.430
Do you want to find him?

37:02.431 --> 37:05.000
Do you mind if I stick around
Storybrooke and look?

37:05.001 --> 37:07.645
I think that'd be great.

37:08.904 --> 37:10.839
[ panting ]

37:10.840 --> 37:13.896
Rumple... his heart.
He said it's almost gone.

37:16.012 --> 37:17.846
And, uh...

37:17.847 --> 37:20.113
He said we're in danger.

37:25.788 --> 37:28.423
<i>Hook: He tried to use the hat
to free himself from the dagger.</i>

37:28.424 --> 37:31.059
<i>Apprentice:
This is not unlike that.</i>

37:31.060 --> 37:33.962
We're pulling the darkness
from him and containing it.

37:33.963 --> 37:36.298
Does that mean
that his heart will be healed?

37:36.299 --> 37:39.034
Perhaps...
if the strength is there.

37:39.035 --> 37:40.902
This is more dark power

37:40.903 --> 37:43.672
than the hat has
ever been asked to contain.

37:43.673 --> 37:45.573
Do what you need to do.

37:45.574 --> 37:49.444
"Purest evil, blackest bloom,

37:49.445 --> 37:51.779
darkness, too, can find its doom."

37:51.780 --> 37:53.415
[ squish ]

37:53.416 --> 37:55.235
[ heartbeat ]

38:02.992 --> 38:05.760
"Never dying, but contained,

38:05.761 --> 38:08.863
bound inside the falcon's chamber,

38:08.864 --> 38:12.867
shorn of anger, thornless danger,

38:12.868 --> 38:16.166
there forever to remain."

38:34.523 --> 38:36.652
[ heartbeat continues ]

38:41.097 --> 38:42.572
[ grunts ]

38:45.968 --> 38:47.478
He's barely breathing.

38:48.771 --> 38:51.806
Rumplestiltskin was the Dark One
for centuries.

38:51.807 --> 38:55.895
His return to the man
he used to be will not be easy.

38:57.113 --> 38:58.847
This will preserve him

38:58.848 --> 39:00.915
until we discern
if we can help him.

39:00.916 --> 39:02.050
"If"?

39:02.051 --> 39:04.152
[ whooshing ]

39:04.153 --> 39:06.213
Everybody step back.

39:20.636 --> 39:23.143
[ gagging ]

39:56.872 --> 39:58.773
Mom, dad!
Go after it!

39:58.774 --> 40:00.542
Go!
I'll be right there.

40:00.543 --> 40:04.045
Help me
make him comfortable.

40:04.046 --> 40:06.147
[ grunts ]

40:06.148 --> 40:08.950
What was that?

40:08.951 --> 40:14.889
[ weakly ] Long before...
Your stories began...

40:14.890 --> 40:17.959
The sorcerer
battled the darkness.

40:17.960 --> 40:23.998
He was able to keep it
from consuming the realms.

40:23.999 --> 40:26.234
He tethered it
to a human soul

40:26.235 --> 40:30.116
that could be controlled
with a dagger.

40:32.241 --> 40:33.992
The Dark One.

40:36.712 --> 40:39.981
The sorcerer is the only one
with the power

40:39.982 --> 40:42.183
to destroy the darkness
once and for all

40:42.184 --> 40:44.953
before it destroys
everything.

40:44.954 --> 40:46.888
Where is he?
Who is he?

40:46.889 --> 40:50.225
He's far, far from here.

40:50.226 --> 40:52.060
Find him.

40:52.061 --> 40:54.705
His name is...

40:55.798 --> 40:57.308
Merlin.

40:59.101 --> 41:03.204
You must... Stop...

41:03.205 --> 41:06.608
The darkness.

41:06.609 --> 41:10.112
Find... Merlin.

41:12.047 --> 41:15.116
[ panting ]

41:15.117 --> 41:16.117
Where is it?!

41:16.118 --> 41:17.151
We don't know.

41:17.152 --> 41:19.316
It just disappeared
into the night.

41:20.990 --> 41:22.290
<i>Regina: Hey, what's going on?</i>

41:22.291 --> 41:24.992
The Dark One... it's no longer
tethered to the crocodile.

41:24.993 --> 41:26.094
What?!

41:26.170 --> 41:27.920
Where the hell is it?

41:33.602 --> 41:35.003
It hasn't gone anywhere.

41:35.004 --> 41:40.054
The darkness...
it's surrounding us.

41:42.311 --> 41:43.993
[ gasps ]

41:46.915 --> 41:48.494
<i>Robin: Regina!</i>

41:53.989 --> 41:54.989
What's it doing?!

41:54.990 --> 41:56.925
What darkness does...

41:56.926 --> 41:59.192
Snuffing out the light.

42:00.262 --> 42:01.669
I'm not gonna let it.

42:04.099 --> 42:07.019
That's not gonna work
on this thing!

42:07.703 --> 42:08.803
The Apprentice told me

42:08.804 --> 42:11.005
we have to do
what the sorcerer did!

42:11.006 --> 42:13.272
We have to tether it
to a person to contain it!

42:14.143 --> 42:16.375
Emma! No!

42:18.614 --> 42:20.748
[ voice breaking ]
There has to be another way!

42:20.749 --> 42:23.585
There isn't.

42:23.586 --> 42:26.986
You've worked to hard to have
your happiness destroyed.

42:28.157 --> 42:29.412
No!

42:29.558 --> 42:31.960
You figured out how to take
the darkness out of me once.

42:31.961 --> 42:35.063
[ voice breaking ]
You need to do it again...

42:35.064 --> 42:36.127
As heroes.

42:37.866 --> 42:40.001
<i>Hook: Emma! Emma, please!</i>

42:40.002 --> 42:41.302
No.

42:41.303 --> 42:43.088
Don't do this,

42:45.708 --> 42:47.046
I love you.

42:49.678 --> 42:50.278
No!

42:50.279 --> 42:52.098
[ grunts ]

43:02.224 --> 43:04.147
Aah!

43:08.964 --> 43:10.784
Aaaaaah!

43:13.769 --> 43:17.032
[ groans ]

